+ lox, in both its stages.Both stages have a 3/1 mass<br>
ratio , are reusable, and have a specific impulse of 450 seconds.All stages, are made of Titanium metal.<br>
2. The whole vehicle has a mass of 3,000,000 kilograms.<br>
Stage 1 has 2,000,000 kilograms of fuel stored in two<br>
tianium metal tanks with a total mass of 400,000 kilograms.<br>
Stage 1 is driven by 19 reusable  space shuttle main engines.<br>
Total first stage  thrust is 7,600,000 pounds.<br>
3. 120,000 kilograms of mass are available for these engines.<br>
4.Stage 2 has a mass of 480,000 kilograms.<br>
5. Stage 2 is driven by 3 space shuttle main engines.<br>
6.Stage has 320,000 kilograms of fuel stored in two <br>
titanium metal tanks with a total mass of 64,000 kilograms.<br>
7.12,000 kilograms of mass is availible for its three engines.<br>
8. This gives a minimium useful payload  of 84,000<br>
 kilograms which can be placed in a 5904 mile high earth<br>
 orbit.If the payload carries nuclear componets this orbit<br>
is a nuclear safe orbit.<br>
9.A heavier payload then this  could be placed in a lower orbit then this by this machine, but should not have nuclear componets in a much lower orbit then this..<br>
10. This can be a module to go into leo , or it can be an <br>
84,000 kilogram space shuttle orbiter.<br>
11. This rocket is my personal design. In my pesonal rocket designs this is my personal equivelent of the Saturn 5 moon rocket.<br>
12. Stage one is recovered by parachutes after burn out.<br>
Stage 2 is either a module permanetly placed in earth orbit,<br>
or it is a reusabale space shuttle style orbiter, that has a ceramic blanket (not tyles) type heat shield,and is made of<br>
titanium metal. <br>
 13. The payload can be a D-100 class space ship that is<br>
equipped with advanced propulsion , and is launched into<br>
earth orbit as the third  stage of this rocket. Depending on <br>
the nature, and the performance of its advanced propulsion<br>
system  this third stage D-100 vehicle  can travel to the moon, all the nine planets, or even the stars . The D-100<br>
always begins its journey from earth orbit<br>
  Questions, comments, discussian about this.<br>
?<br>
Tim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/1/03 1:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=819.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: This is my design for an HLV or HLSV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Stage 1 is driven by 19 reusable space shuttle main engines.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
