The Russian soyuz launch vehicle uses 16 engines to lift<br>
off. The Russian A-1 sattalite launcher uses 32 engines<br>
in the first stage. We americans have used at most 5 <br>
expendable engines per stage before but there is ample precedent in astronautics for 19 engines. In this design<br>
 the 19 reusable space shuttle engines are required to develop enough first stage thrust to lift off the pad.<br>
You can not use expendable engines in a reusable launch vehicle.*<br>
